Description: Counter made of a reused pottery sherd from Nile clay. The edges are very well smoothed with a rectangular section. The upper side shows two incised lines forming a cross. The incised lines were filled with a black substance (charcoal?) that has partly fallen out.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D16.K, Mound β, sand
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 213-214)
